SpeakingAnki — AGPL-3.0 notice

This project implements Anki-compatible collection I/O and SM-2 scheduling
semantics derived from the open-source Anki ecosystem (ankitects/anki, AGPL-3.0).

If you distribute this application (including TestFlight / App Store), you must
provide corresponding source code under AGPL-3.0 terms.

When the optional Rust `rslib` XCFramework is linked, the AGPL obligation is
strict and unavoidable for any distributed binary.

Azure Speech and DashScope/Qwen are third-party cloud services; their SDKs/APIs
are subject to their own licenses and terms. API keys must not be committed.
